	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=162930><span id= >sabarazz</span></a><br><span id=notbold>2 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [4.40]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Determining who gets these in a group shouldn't be that difficult.&nbsp;&nbsp;There are a few (COMMON SENSE) rules to keep in mind though.  Sure, the 0.0 wt is outstanding!  Who wouldn't want to wear an all/all 10ac +stats with 0.0 wt?  If there happens to be a lot of loot. . . loot that a monk can't grab due to his/her wt restriction. . . then go ahead and let em have it. . . but. . . if it's been fair game all game. . .everyone should roll on it.  I'm a Monk of the 27th Scale. . and when I loot something better than what I have. . .I keep the slightly lesser stuff for trade purposes later on. . . . granted that run to the bank might be tedious. . . . but you can work something our for later in the game.  .. . that's what tells are for.  This happens to be my first and only character .. . . and I would love to get a hold of any spider fur anything. . . but if I'm  in a group. . . let's face it. . most people in my groups all have a need for it.  I am a non-tweaked character that's had to punch kick and claw my way to where I am at. . . . but I also understand that at some point. . . so did almost everyone else that plays this GAME.  If I happen to have an unlucky roll once in a while. . . .I will roll on something another party member needs.  ..and then if I win. . work out a trade.  Common Sense.  Keep in mind also, that this is still just a game.  It is addictive (I'm hooked for life!) it can be frustrating.  .but never lose sight that it's still a game.  Have fun with it.  </p>&nbsp;<br><br>Sabarazz Swiftfists<br>Monk of the 27th Scale</td></tr>
